# Frontend (Next.js 15)

## Structure

```
frontend/src/
├── app/                    # App Router pages
│   ├── page.tsx            # Home
│   ├── queries/new/        # Submit query
│   └── queries/[id]/       # Job detail + React Flow
├── components/
│   ├── ui/                 # shadcn/ui
│   ├── workflow/           # React Flow pipeline nodes/edges
│   └── dashboard/          # Synthesis viewer, sources, cost
├── hooks/useJobStream.ts   # SSE subscription
├── lib/api-client.ts       # Typed fetch (openapi-typescript)
└── types/                  # Generated from OpenAPI
```

## Patterns

- App Router, Server Components by default; `"use client"` only when needed (React Flow, SSE, forms)
- shadcn/ui for all UI primitives — don't reinvent buttons, dialogs, etc.
- API types generated from backend OpenAPI — don't hand-write request/response types
- Env: `NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL` for API base

## React Flow pipeline

Node states: `pending` → `running` → `completed` | `failed`

Update nodes from SSE events keyed by `correlation_id`. Show per-stage duration and agent name on click.

## Key pages

- `/` — landing + recent queries
- `/queries/new` — form: topic (required), depth, max_sources
- `/queries/[id]` — React Flow + synthesis markdown + sources + cost panel

## Real-time

Prefer SSE over WebSocket (ADR-010). `useJobStream(jobId)` hook connects to `/api/v1/queries/{id}/stream`. No auth headers — API uses implicit mock user (ADR-013).
